Message.message: I can't carry two kids at once for my leg hurts! I should bring one to safety first.
You failed to keep the child alive. Please restart the level and try again.
Hans: I cannot leave the child here, I must rescue every child I find.
Mary: Could you carry Half to the river, Hans?
Hans: Sure, sister. Come on!
Hans: Do you know what is at the other side of the river, Half?
Half: No, what is it?
Hans: It's Fircone town, they are our allies, and actually we owe them this calm morning!
Half: Too boring, better tell me how you lost your leg, uncle Hans!
Hans: Maybe next time... Hey, Paul!
Paul: Hello, neighbour!
Hans: (wakes up) Holy crap!
Hans: It's not a dream! The ammunition depot just blew up!
Hans: This can mean only one thing - they betrayed us...
The stripe above the level shows the timing of bomb drops
Hans: This is really bad, I must hurry to make sure Half and Mary are in safety!
Hans: No doubt, all drops are carefully targeted.
Hans: But what kind of a scum put all those flare marks?!
Hans: These fuel barrels are the same ones we provided to Fircone.
Hans: For their planes.
Hans: Most streets are obstructed, but I will find a way out.
Hans: I hate it when I can't stop bastards on planes to bomb everything around!
Hans: Outskirts. I'm almost there.
Hans: The cliff. I see a kid. This should be Half...
Half: You're the hero, uncle Hans!
Hans: Where is your mom?
Half: That over-the-river man... He punched her... and forced to go with him!..
Half: But I ran away...
Hans: Son of a!..
Hans: Stay here, Half! I'll go talk to Paul.
Hans: Hey you!
Paul: Get lost or I'll shoot! You'll never understand!
Hans: Rest in peace, my dear neighbour. You were buried right at the place you marked.
Mary: Hans!
Mary: Did you see Half?
Hans: Don't worry, sister, he's safe.
THE END
